Options
*******

`ADOC' reads the command line from left to right and collects filenames
and options before it starts processing your input.  The filenames are
queued and processed in the same order as they appear in the command
line.  The list-file option `@' is replaced by the contents of the list
file read in top-down order. If no input files are specified `ADOC'
will read from the standard input stream.


 @{" Autodoc Options " Link "Autodoc Options"}        `Autodoc' output only
 @{" IO Options " Link "IO Options"}             both `Autodoc' and `Texinfo' output
 @{" Texinfo Options " Link "Texinfo Options"}        `Texinfo' output only
 @{" Warning Options " Link "Warning Options"}        influencing `ADOC''s pedanticness
 @{" Miscellaneous Options " Link "Miscellaneous Options"}  everything else


